About TrustSwap (SWAP)

TrustSwap is a decentralized finance (DeFi) trading platform that was launched in July 2021. Its native cryptocurrency, SWAP, is an ERC-20 utility token that is compatible with the Ethereum blockchain. TrustSwap offers services for both businesses and everyday users. 
SWAP is used within the TrustSwap ecosystem for paying network fees, staking, governance, and participating in LaunchPad. LaunchPad is a service that supports new projects with fundraising, smart contract development, token launches, and marketing.
Paying for platform fees with SWAP token instead of ETH qualifies you for a discount of up to 50%. This also supports the token’s deflationary model, where 10% is burned, 10% goes to a developer fund, and 80% is distributed as staking rewards, ensuring a steady reduction in circulating supply for SWAP over.
SWAP token holders are usually DeFi traders and crypto project creators who want to participate in the TrustSwap ecosystem.

  • What is the TrustSwap Launchpad?

    TrustSwap LaunchPad is a service that supports new crypto projects with fundraising, smart contract development, token launches, and marketing.

  • What are TrustSwap SmartLocks?

    TrustSwap SmartLocks are smart contracts that securely lock tokens/liquidity until a predefined schedule is met. It helps DeFi projects prevent rug pulls, exit scams, and ensures transparency in token distribution.

  • What are TrustSwap SmartSwaps?

    SmartSwaps is a peer-to-peer escrow service that facilitates the secure exchange of digital assets between users without requiring a middleman. It does this by ensuring that funds are only released when the agreed conditions are met by parties involved.

  • How do I add TrustSwap to MetaMask?

    MetaMask automatically displays popular tokens like TrustSwap（SWAP）within your wallet. If you are not seeing your SWAP in MetaMask, you can manually add it using the "Add to MetaMask" button above, over the price chart. Please remember that you first need to install MetaMask extension if you are on a PC or Mac (desktop computer). If you are on mobile, please check out our MetaMask Support guide here for more info.

  • How do I buy TrustSwap?

    Buying TrustSwap (SWAP) in MetaMask wallet is speedy, simple, and safe. You can buy TrustSwap (SWAP) tokens directly in MetaMask using payment methods like a credit card, debit card, bank account, Apple Pay, Google Pay, or PayPal. There's no need for centralised exchanges. Select from thousands of your favourite tokens to buy on over 15 networks including Ethereum, Binance Smart Chain, Linea, Base, and more.

  • How do I sell TrustSwap?

    MetaMask makes it easy to sell your TrustSwap (SWAP) and convert your crypto to cash. You can exchange from MetaMask wallet directly to your debit card, credit card, PayPal, or bank account. By removing unnecessary steps and cutting excess fees, offramping your digital assets is fast and simple.

  • How do I swap TrustSwap?

    Swapping SWAP is simple and cost-effective with MetaMask. Choose from thousands of your favourite tokens across ten networks including Ethereum, Solana, Linea, Base, and Arbitrum. MetaMask Swaps also include gas fees right in your quotes, making swapping crypto as smooth as can be.

  • How do I bridge TrustSwap?

    Bridging crypto across chains allows you to move tokens from one network to another. With MetaMask, bridging TrustSwap (SWAP) is easy, secure, and cost-effective. Our aggregator finds the most efficient routes to move your digital assets from one chain to another. And with cross-chain swapping, bridging and swapping can take place at the same time in a single transaction. Meaning: instead of bridging SWAP from chain A and wrapping or unwrapping it on chain B, you can swap SWAP from chain A to a second token on chain B, all in one move.

  • What can you do with TrustSwap?

    With TrustSwap, you can send and receive SWAP, the network's native token, and use it to pay transaction fees on certain networks. SWAP is supported in decentralised apps for trading, staking, yield optimisation, and payments. You can participate in DeFi protocols, bridge assets between networks, or use SWAP in select web3 financial strategies, all with Ethereum-compatible speed and flexibility.

  • How do I trade TrustSwap for other cryptocurrencies?

    Trading TrustSwap (SWAP) for ETH, WBTC, or SOL can be done directly in MetaMask. For more information on how to swap SWAP, head to MetaMask Support.
